obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4021)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4021&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prevention of`
  line `Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint, and different dates ^1 may be appointed for different States and for the`
  line `different provisions contained in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2 1st April, 1961, vide Notification No.S.O.823, dated the 1st April, 1961, in respect of the State of Punjab and the Union`
  line `territory of Andaman and Nicobar Island, see Gazette of India 1961, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `1st September, 1961, vide Notification No. S.O. 2061, dated the 25th August, 1961, for Chapters I and II in respect of the`
  line `States of Assam, Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Gujarat, Kerala, Madras, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Mysore, Orissa, Uttar`
  line `Pradesh and West Bengal and the Union territories of Delhi, Manipur and Tripura, see Gazette of India, 1961, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `2nd October, 1961, vide Notification No. S.O. 2286, dated 15th September 1961, Chapters I and II in respect of the Union`
  line `territory of Himachal Pradesh, Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `26th January, 1962, vide Notification No. S.O. 21, dated 28th December, 1961, provisions of Chapters I and II in respect`
  line `of the State of Rajasthan, see Gazette of India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `15th July, 1963, vide Notification No. S.O. 2000, dated 11th July, 1963, Chapter IV in respect of the States of Assam,`
  line `Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Gujarat, Kerala, Madras, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Mysore, Orissa, Rajasthan, Uttar Pradesh`
  line `and West Bengal and in respect of the Union territories of Delhi, Himachal Pradesh, Manipur and Tripura, see Gazette of`
  line `India, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `20th November, 1963, vide Notification No. S.O. 3160, dated 29th October, 1963, Chapters III and VI in respect of the`
  line `States of Assam, Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, Gujarat, Kerala, Madras, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh, Mysore, Orissa,`
  line `Rajasthan and Uttar Pradesh and in respect of the Union territories of Delhi, Himachal Pradesh, Manipur and Tripura,`
  line `see Gazette of India. Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
  line
  line `24th May, 1977, vide Notification No. S.O. 1902, dated 24th May 1977, provisions of Chapter V in respect of all the`
  line `States and the Union territories to which this Act extends (except the State of Jammu and Kashmir).`
  line
  line `This Act has been extended to Goa, Daman and Diu by Reg. 11 of 1963, s. 3 and Sch. and comes into force in Pondicherry`
  line `vide Reg. 7 of 1963, s. 3 and Sch.I (w.e.f. 1-10-1963). and brought into force in Dadra and Nagar Haveli by Reg. 6 of`
  line `1963, s. 2 and Sch. I (w.e.f. 1-7-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4022)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 26 of 1982, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4022&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "animal" means any living creature other than a human being;`
  line
  line `^1[(b) "Board" means the Board established under section 4, and as reconstituted from time to`
  line `time under section 5A;]`
  line
  line `(c) "captive animal" means any animal (not being a domestic animal) which is in captivity or`
  line `confinement, whether permanent or temporary, or which is subjected to any appliance or`
  line `contrivance for the purpose of hindering or preventing its escape from captivity or confinement or`
  line `which is pinioned or which is or appears to be maimed;`
  line
  line `(d) "domestic animal" means any animal which is tamed or which has been or is being`
  line `sufficiently tamed to serve some purpose for the use of man or which, although it neither has been`
  line `nor is being nor is intended to be so tamed, is or has become in fact wholly or partly tamed;`
  line
  line `(e) "local authority" means a municipal committee, district board or other authority for the`
  line `time being invested by law with the control and administration of any matters within a specified`
  line `local area;`
  line
  line `(f) "owner", used with reference to an animal, includes not only the owner but also any other`
  line `person for the time being in possession or custody of the animal, whether with or without the`
  line `consent of the owner;`
  line
  line `(g) "phooka" or "doom dev" includes any process of introducing air or any substance into the`
  line `female organ of a milch animal with the object of drawing off from the animal any secretion of`
  line milk;
  line
  line `(h) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) "street" includes any way, road, lane, square, court, alley, passage or open space, whether a`
  line `thoroughfare or not, to which the public have access.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2.--In section 2 of the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals Act, 1960`
  line `(Central Act 59 of 1960) (hereinafter referred to as the Principal Act),--`
  line
  line `(i) after clause (a), the following shall be inserted, namely:---`
  line
  line `"(aa) "Bulls race or Bullock cart race" means any form of bulls race including race of Bullock`
  line `cart as a traditional sports involving Bulls whether tied to cart with the help of wooden yoke or not (in`
  line `whatever name called) normally held as a part of tradition and culture in the state on such days and`
  line `places, as may be notified by the State Government."; and`
  line
  line `(ii) after clause (d), the following shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(dd) "Kambala" means the traditional sports event involving Buffalo's (male) race normally`
  line `held as a part of tradition and culture in the state on such days and places, as may be notified by the`
  line `State Government."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 2 of 2018, s. 2].`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 2 of 59 of 1960.--In section 2 of the Prevention of Cruelty to animals Act, 1960 (59 of 1960), in its application to the State of Maharashtra (hereinafter referred to as “the principal Act”), after clause (b), the following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `“(bb) “bullock cart race” means an event involving bulls or bullocks to conduct a race, whether tied to cart with the help of wooden yoke or not (by whatever name called), with or without a cartman with a view to follow tradition and culture on such days and in any District where it is being traditionally held at such places, as may be previously approved by the District Collector, and also known as “Bailgada Sharyat”, “Chhakadi” and “shankarpat” in the State of Maharashtra;”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 45 of 2017, s. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4023)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Duties of persons having charge of animals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4023&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of every person having the`
  line `care or charge of any animal to take all reasonable measures to ensure the well-being of such animal`
  line `and to prevent the infliction upon such animal of unnecessary pain or suffering.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3.--Section 3 of the principal Act, shall be re-numbered as sub-section`
  line `(1) of that section and after sub-section (1) as so renumbered, the following sub-section shall be`
  line `inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) conduct of "Kambala" or "Bulls race`
  line `or Bullock cart race" shall be permitted, subject to condition that no unnecessary pain or suffering is`
  line `caused to the animals, by the person incharge of that animal used to conduct "Kambala" or "Bulls`
  line `race or Bullock cart race" as the case may be and subject to such other conditions as may be specified,`
  line `by the State Government, by notification."`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 2 of 2018, s. 3].`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of 59 of 1960.--Section 3 of the principal Act shall be re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof; and after sub-section (1) as so re-numbered, the following sub-sections shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the bullock cart race may be conducted with the prior permission of the Collector, subject to the condition that no pain or suffering as envisaged by or under the Act is caused to the animal by any person or person in charge of the animal used to conduct bullock cart race and subject to such other conditions as may be prescribed by rules under section 38B by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person or person in charge of the animals conducts bullock cart race in contravention of the conditions laid down in sub-section (2) or rules made thereunder relating to the bullock cart race or causes pain or suffering to the animal, he shall be punished with fine which may extend upto rupees five lakhs or imprisonment for a term which may extend upto three years.".`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 45 of 2017, s. 3].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4024)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Establishment of Animal Welfare Board of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "Animal Welfare Board" (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4024&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the promotion of animal`
  line `welfare generally and for the purpose of protecting animals from being subjected to unnecessary`
  line `pain or suffering, in particular, there shall be established by the Central Government, as soon as may`
  line `be after the commencement of this Act, a Board to be called the ^1[Animal Welfare Board of India].`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with`
  line `power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and may by its`
  line `name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4025)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4025&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall consist of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Inspector-General of Forests, Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) the Animal Husbandry Commissioner to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `^1[(ba) two persons to represent respectively the Ministries of the Central Government dealing`
  line `with home affairs and education, to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(bb) one person to represent the Indian Board for Wild Life, to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(bc) three persons who, in the opinion of the Central Government, are or have been actively`
  line `engaged in animal welfare work and are well-known humanitarians, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;]`
  line
  line `(c) one person to represent such association of veterinary practitioners as in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government ought to be represented on the Board, to be elected by that association in the`
  line `prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(d) two persons to represent practitioners of modern and indigenous systems of medicine, to`
  line `be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `^2[(e) one person to represent each of such two municipal corporations as in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government ought to be represented on the Board, to be elected by each of the said`
  line `corporations in the prescribed manner;]`
  line
  line `(f) one person to represent each of such three organisations actively interested in animal`
  line `welfare as in the opinion of the Central Government ought to be represented on the Board, to be`
  line `chosen by each of the said organisations in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(g) one person to represent each of such three societies dealing with prevention of cruelty to`
  line `animals as in the opinion of the Central Government ought to be represented on the Board, to be`
  line `chosen in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(h) three persons to be nominated by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) six members of Parliament, four to be elected by the House of the People (Lok Sabha) and`
  line `two by the Council of States (Rajya Sabha).`
  line
  line `(2) Any of the persons referred to in clause (a) or ^3[clause (b) or clause (ba) or clause (bb)] of`
  line `sub-section (1) may depute any other person to attend any of the meetings of the Board.`
  line
  line `^4[(3) The Central Government shall nominate one of the members of the Board to be its Chairman`
  line `and another member of the Board to be its Vice-Chairman.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 26 of 1982, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for clause (e) (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "clause (b)" (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  line
  line `4 Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (4026)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Reconstitution of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4026&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Reconstitution of the Board.-- (1) In order that the Chairman and other members of the`
  line `Board hold office till the same date and that their terms of office come to an end on the same date, the`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, reconstitute, as soon as may be after`
  line `the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (Amendment) Act, 1982 (26 of 1982) comes into force, the`
  line Board.
  line
  line `(2) The Board as reconstituted under sub-section (1) shall be reconstituted from time to time on`
  line `the expiration of every third year from the date of its reconstitution under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be included amongst the members of the Board reconstituted under`
  line `sub-section (1), all persons who immediately before the date on which such reconstitution is to take`
  line `effect, are members of the Board but such persons shall hold office only for the unexpired portion of`
  line `the term for which they would have held office if such reconstitution had not been made and the`
  line `vacancies arising as a result of their ceasing to be members of the Board shall be filled up as casual`
  line `vacancies for the remaining period of the term of the Board as so reconstituted:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply in relation to any person who ceases to be a`
  line `member of the Board by virtue of the amendment made in sub-section (1) of section 5 by`
  line `sub-clause (ii) of clause (a) of section 5 of the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1982 (26 of 1982).]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4027)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office and conditions of service of members of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 26 of 1982, s.7, for section 6 (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4027&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Term of office and conditions of service of members of the Board.-- (1) The term for`
  line `which the Board may be reconstituted under section 5A shall be three years from the date of the`
  line `reconstitution and the Chairman and other members of the Board as so reconstituted shall hold office`
  line `till the expiry of the term for which the Board has been so reconstituted.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office of an ex officio member shall continue so long as he holds the office by`
  line `virtue of which he is such a member;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of office of a member elected or chosen under clause (c), clause (e), clause (f),`
  line `clause (g), clause (h) or clause (i) of section 5 to represent any body of persons shall come to an`
  line `end as soon as he ceases to be a member of the body which elected him or in respect of which he`
  line `was chosen;`
  line
  line `(c) the term of office of a member appointed, nominated, elected or chosen to fill a casual`
  line `vacancy shall continue for the remainder of the term of office of the member in whose place he is`
  line `appointed, nominated, elected or chosen;`
  line
  line `(d) the Central Government may, at any time, remove for reasons to be recorded in writing a`
  line `member from office after giving him a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the`
  line `proposed removal and any vacancy caused by such removal shall be treated as casual vacancy for`
  line `the purpose of clause (c).`
  line
  line `(3) The members of the Board shall receive such allowances, if any, as the Board may, subject to`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government, provide by regulations made in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(4) No act done or proceeding taken by the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the`
  line `existence of any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution of, the Board and in particular, and without`
  line `prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, during the period intervening between the expiry of the`
  line `term for which the Board has been reconstituted under section 5A and its further reconstitution under`
  line `that section, the ex officio members of the Board shall discharge all the powers and functions of the`
  line Board.]
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4028)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Secretary and other employees of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. The words "one of its officers to be" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4028&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall appoint`
  line `^1*** the Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the Board`
  line `may appoint such number of other officers and employees as may be necessary for the exercise of its powers and the discharge of its functions and may determine the terms and conditions of service of`
  line `such officers and other employees by regulations made by it with the previous approval of the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4029)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Funds of the Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4029&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The funds of the Board shall consist of grants made to it from time to`
  line `time by the Government and of contributions, donations, subscriptions, bequests, gifts and the like`
  line `made to it by any local authority or by any other person.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4030)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Board .`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734&sectionId=4030&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00001_196059_1517807317734
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Board shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to keep the law in force in India for the prevention of cruelty to animals under constant`
  line `study and advise the Government on the amendments to be undertaken in any such law from time`
  line `to time;`
  line
  line `(b) to advise the Central Government on the making of rules under this Act with a view to`
  line `preventing unnecessary pain or suffering to animals generally, and more particularly when they`
  line `are being transported from one place to another or when they are used as performing animals or`
  line `when they are kept in captivity or confinement;`
  line
  line `(c) to advise the Government or any local authority or other person on improvements in the`
  line `design of vehicles so as to lessen the burden on draught animals;`
  line
  line `(d) to take all such steps as the Board may think fit for ^1[amelioration of animals] by`
  line `encouraging, or providing for, the construction of sheds, water-troughs and the like and by`
  line `providing for veterinary assistance to animals;`
  line
  line `(e) to advise the Government or any local authority or other person in the design of`
  line `slaughter-houses or in the maintenance of slaughter-houses or in connection with slaughter of`
  line `animals so that unnecessary pain or suffering, whether physical or mental, is eliminated in the`
  line `pre-slaughter stages as far as possible, and animals are killed, wherever necessary, in as humane a`
  line `manner as possible;`
  line
  line `(f) to take all such steps as the Board may think fit to ensure that unwanted animals are`
  line `destroyed by local authorities, whenever it is necessary to do so, either instantaneously or after`
  line `being rendered insensible to pain or suffering;`
  line
  line `(g) to encourage, by the grant of financial assistance or otherwise ^2[the formation or`
  line `establishment of pinjrapoles, rescue homes, animal shelters, sanctuaries and the like] where`
  line `animals and birds may find a shelter when they have become old and useless or when they need`
  line protection;
  line
  line `(h) to co-operate with, and co-ordinate the work of, associations or bodies established for the`
  line `purpose of preventing unnecessary pain or suffering to animals or for the protection of animals`
  line `and birds;`
  line
  line `(i) to give financial and other assistance to animal welfare organisations functioning in any`
  line `local area or to encourage the formation of animal welfare organisations in any local area which`
  line `shall work under the general supervision and guidance of the Board;`
  line
  line `(j) to advise the Government on matters relating to the medical care and attention which may`
  line `be provided in animal, hospitals and to give financial and other assistance to animal hospitals`
  line `whenever the Board thinks it necessary to do so;`
  line
  line `(k) to impart education in relation to the humane treatment of animals and to encourage the`
  line `formation of public opinion against the infliction of unnecessary pain or suffering to animals and`
  line `for the promotion of animal welfare by means of lectures, books, posters, cinematographic`
  line `exhibitions and the like;`
  line
  line `(l) to advise the Government on any matter connected with animal welfare or the prevention`
  line `of infliction of unnecessary pain or suffering on animals.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 26 of 1982, s. 9, for "ameliorating the condition of beasts of burden" (w.e.f. 30-7-1982).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "the formation of pinjrapoles, sanctuaries and the like" (w.e.f. 30-7-1982)`
